Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams} in the pan, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break
up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after
handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%grams}.

Halve the @Burger Buns{2}.

Toast the buns in your #toaster{}.

Once the pork has browned, stir in the @Beef Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} and @Water{50%milliliters}.

Simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Top your bun bases with the pork mince, cheese and @Burger Sauce{45%grams} - as
much as you'd like. Sandwich shut with the lids.

Serve the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%grams} on the side.

Drizzle with @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml}. Scatter over the @Pumpkin Seeds{15%grams}.

Enjoy!